<p>Multiple epiphyseal dysplasia is characterized by early-onset short stature, waddling gait, and stiffness and/or pain in the knees and sometimes other joints (Muragaki et al., 1996).</p>

<p>For a general phenotypic description and a discussion of genetic heterogeneity of multiple epiphyseal dysplasia, see EDM1.</p>

<p>[Muragaki, Y., Mariman, E. C. M., van Beersum, S. E. C., Perala, M., van Mourik, J. B. A., Warman, M. L., Olsen, B. R., Hamel, B. C. J. A mutation in the gene encoding the alpha-2 chain of the fibril-associated collagen IX, COL9A2, causes multiple epiphyseal dysplasia (EDM2). Nature Genet. 12: 103-105, 1996.]<br/></p>